<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-28T10:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-28T10:30:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.5151/277: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-28T11:00:00-04:30">August 28, 1937—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>755. My 753, August 27, 5 p.m. The Director of the Exchange Bureau
                            informed me this morning that virtually all peseta deposits awaiting
                            dollar exchange are in private banks and that the banks and not the
                            Government are responsible therefor. He was, of course, not aware of my
                            conversation with Negrín yesterday.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>